HEADWORD: Millinery
<hw>Mil"li*ner*y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
articles made or sold by milliners, as headdresses, hats or bonnets,
laces, ribbons, and the like.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The business of work of a milliner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Millinet</ent>⟦br⟧
